message.content: We complete the square on the right-hand side by adding 20 to both sides, giving $x^2+y^2 - 7 = 2y-8x+21$.  We can rewrite this as  \[(x+4)^2+(y-1)^2=33.\]This equation represents the graph of a circle centered at $(-4,1)$ with radius $\sqrt{33}$.  The area of this circle is $\pi (\sqrt{33})^2 = \boxed{33\pi}$.
